caption: Delicious, fresh, healthy food. Not much else you need to know. Indoor dining is allowed at limited capacity, take out is quick and efficient. Staff is courteous and food was prepared accurately.
The food was tasty and the staff friendly. Spent $15 for a full plate of vegan food and a bowl of lentil soup. Left satisfied and full. 10/10 given that not all vegan meals can fill me up for $15
Food was great. Good service
The staff is friendly and the food always good. Recommend.
The food is very good
I think I'd recommend the wrap over the pita-pocket. But pretty good food for a reasonable price. Staff was nice when we went and made the experience a good one.

I dream of this place and it's falafel! I just got diagnosed with elevated LDL so have to watch my saturated fat and cholesterol intake. That eliminates most food I can order out, so I've been relying on Mediterranean a lot because it is healthy but also has flavor, something an american food based low-fat diet is grossly devoid of. The PLATES here, omg. So many delicious ingredients you can have! I tried another place that had a plate like this but it wasn't as good.

Honest Review of @idreamoffalafel in Chicago 😋 . ✅Great service ✅Nice Staff ✅Clean ✅Banging Food . I’d definitely recommend if you’re ever in the Chicago 👍🏾. Thank you @idreamoffalafel for a great 1st time experience. . #falafel #mediterraneanfood #idof #chicagofood #honestreview
Recently started frequenting this restaurant. The food has been fresh and good. I definitely would recommend it for a quick bite on the go.

One of the best authentic falafel I ever tasted in the U.S. Shawarma not really!, and the reason I say this, it is not cooked the way authentic shawarma is! ( which is similar to gyro)

I am a regular customer at IDOF and I am extremely disappointed with customer service and the food portions at this place. Last time I visited the place I paid $13 for the “all in platter” and the staff gave me tiny portions of chicken and gyro for my protein option. Hopefully, management can do something to fix the wrongdoings of their employees.

Excellent service and high quality, authentic ingredients.  I just ordered delivery and it arrived hot and perfect.  This was the best falafel and chicken shawarma plate I’ve had in a long, long time.  I will definitely order from this location again!

I heard good things about IDOF but my first experience was a big disappointment. I came couple minutes before they opened and I ordered 2 falafels and fries. The gentleman who serviced us grab pita bread from a grocery bag, don't know if it was leftover bread or that's how they store their food and he asked us what we wanted and I told him everything on thats included in the falafel. he only added a pinch of onion and lettuce when I told him everything. The fries was half empty and soggy. Let me just say for 21 dollars and the first customer to walk in, I expected a better service.
Pretty delicious and quick. For a fast food stand, it's pretty solid. I really enjoyed it. The falafel is cooked fresh & in view of the customers.

If zero stars was an option, it would be too kind! We placed an order for a lunch meeting to be delivered at 1pm and the food arrive just as our meeting was ending which was an hour past the delivery time (2pm). Around 1:15 we had to call 7 TIMES before someone picked up. And when they did - no remorse, just excuses and they rushed us off the phone.  When the food was delivered: No napkins, not enough eating utensils, the food was cold. There was no regard for the complete inconvenience or the horrific customer service. I would not recommend this place for delivery orders and I will NEVER go here again, despite the food being decent. Customer service is too important to me.
They skimpy on the meat and a constant, "and what else and what else and what else...

Today,January 25th at 1.45pm,l.got here & found a slender built young fella as cashier...he didn't look white & he wasn't black.  I always eat here & l always go for the all-in-1 platter. He has the worst customer service manners. There was no one in line,he tells me to wait 6 minutes & while waiting before my food is even prepared, he asks me to pay. I said how do u know what l want cos some sides are chargeable?  I refused & literally told him what to do,l always leave a handsome tip but not today. His attempt at racially profiling me failed. I hope next time l find the wonderful owner l will tell him about my experience

Horrible customer service, doesn’t explain what the items are. Only customers in the restaurant and service took 10 min. Items not fresh, portions extremely small, nickel and dime you to death with extras that aren’t even considered extras at nuff nuff!
Go with the all I'm platter, you get all your meat.

Good food! High quality, fresh, and very clean. I definitely plan on here again soon. I had the Mediterranean chicken salad, which was very satisfying but light. My SO had the falafel wrap, which he enjoyed very much. Sauces and toppings were also very tasty and fresh.

The food and the service is pretty good. I just wish they would add a little more meat to the shwarmas. I'm not sure if it was because I came in near closing hours or if that is just it is, but that was my experience. Other than that it's pretty easy to order and the food taste great.
Great food, like to eat falafel!
Good food! I like to eat Falafel And fries👍

Placed an order online. Arrived fifteen minutes later when it was supposed to be ready. The place was completely empty and they had not started preparing my order yet. The falafel was fried which is fine, however it tasted greasy. The "bread" they use for the wrap is a plain wrap so I'm not sure why they try to play it off like it's something special. Also, it was $11.50 for a medium sized wrap. It was edible, but I was disappointed and won't be back.

Health option, quick, friendly service, fairly clean, fresh veggies. Priced a bit more than other places but it's the city so about right. Down side, they didn't cook the pita bread. The meat was not cut off the spit rotisserie, it was pre-cut earlier and came our of a warmer drawer, not the same!

Conveniently located by my job, I wanted to get something quick for lunch. There was a burger place and Idof. So glad with my choice. The food is made to order, clean fresh and tasty. Vegan falafel and tasty chicken. I'm not sure how long they've been open but eat there! It's a fresh alternative to burgers and Italian beef joints ...ijs

I always hit IDOF when I'm superhungry. I love the taste of chicken kebab and portions are perfect for my appetite 😝  I tried falafel as well, they taste very good when fresh but later on it loses it's taste. So, I always go with chicken kebab or shwarma.
Good for a quick healthy bite on Taylor street.

The best part about this place is that they fry the falafel with your order, so it is fresh and crispy. I order hummus plate over a pita pocket since for 2 extra dollars you get much more quantity and control over the toppings. You can mix up the toppings and you will get an even taste, unlike a pita pocket.
Delicious and organic I mean come on what more can you ask for

I love a good smorgasbord, and this place gives a ton of sides, condiments, and variety. Delicious red pepper hummus for which I'd go exclusively. One of my favorite small chain restaurants. Love that meat eaters, vegans, and gluten free friends alike can come together and all have a delicious meal.
Best healthy meal deal

Loved the falafel. AMAZING! Fresh and delicious ingredients! Definitely would recommend it to my friends and family. You get to choose pita, wrap, bowl, or plate. Then choose your protein, toppings, then dips or dressings and hummus. Everything was fresh made to order. Yummy. Highly recommend it.

Great food but unfortunately no respect for customers. I recently ordered via Postmates and for some reason they didn't check the order and by the time the driver was there for pick up, they said they were closing. It's IDOF's fault and I get that mistakes happen but recognize the responsibility to do something to make up for it. Can't you arrange for one meal? At least call and inform the customer. I had to hear this from Postmates.

The menu has some good options for vegans and vegetarians. The chicken shawarma is very satisfying. The staff here move with a sense of urgency and you can see them assemble your food right in front of you. You can dine in with a plate of rice, cabbage, and falafel or take a shawarma wrap on the go. The prices could be lower but the quality, service, and cleanliness of the store make the price a modest one

Bar none the best Mediterranean franchise I’ve had the pleasure of dining with here in Chicago. Get the chicken shawarma plate, it’s reasonably priced, and top quality food that will be sure to leave you satisfied. Even though I find myself to be a picky eater, I’m at this place weekly it seems.

Excellent falafels and better than the ones at Naf Naf. The service was exceptional. Very courteous caring and helpful staff. NAF NAF ones are. Much better and perhaps the only reason to choose naf naf over this. I had a vegetarian bowl and costed about 11$ all inclusive.

The food does not taste very authentic. Very westernized version of Mediterranean food. The kefta kabob was dry and tasted like hamburger meat. The food is pricey for what you get. The falafel did not taste good at all; very gummy and salty. If you're looking for good authentic Mediterranean food, look elsewhere. Paid street parking is available but hard to find. The restaurant is clean. Staff is friendly and welcoming.

Placed an order via grub hub. It wasn't ready when I got there. No one in line. I left with my order. Got home and it was incomplete. I was missing a whole plate. We called and they said they would make it but we would have to come back and pick it up. I was not happy that I had to drive all the way back to the restaurant to pick up the missing plate. There was no sorry or nothing offered to compensate for screwing up the order. This has never happened before but I can't forgive this guy especially when the place wasn't busy at all. There was no excuse for messing up the order.

Love IDOF and was pleasantly surprised that this location is no different than my previous experiences. Went at about 2 o’clock on a Saturday and service was quick and helpful!  Bed of Hummus is the way to go!

Service was very bad   and one employee dropped my sauce on the floor pick that up and put it in my bag and he was wearing the gloves after that used the same gloves for my pita . This was my first experience at idof and last one . Get the crew trained please at least the sanitation part .

I was about to go to Jimmy John's when I saw this place. I generally enjoy Mediterranean food, so I thought I'd give it a try. It was very good; not too different from what I've had at Naf Naf Grill and other places, but I would go back if the opportunity presented itself.

This place is conveniently located in the UIC area, and it’s a nice change of pace from those other chains.  I love the variety that you can get here. You can order falafel, gyro, chicken shawarma, kefta kebab in a bowl, wrap, salad, or hummus. So versatile, and the ingredients taste fresh. I even like the pita chips, and I never get that stuff. The lentil soup is also a must try.  The interior is clean, and the service very friendly and helpful. Order like other fast casual places to eat in or to go.

The food here was absolutely amazing. The ingredients were super fresh and delicious. Its gonna be hard not going here all the time living in this neighborhood. I'm so glad the built an amazing, fresh, Mediterranean restraunt here. It used to be a gross dumpy hookah bar. 10/10 will be back.
